            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;ArrayDeque&lt;/code&gt; is slower than &lt;code&gt;LinkedList&lt;/code&gt; unless all operations are at the same end. It&apos;s OK when used as a stack but it doesn&apos;t make a good queue.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/1840613/jeremy-list&quot; title=&quot;1,726 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Jeremy List&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment48036368_882151&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2015-04-30 02:12:27Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Apr 30, 2015 at 2:12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Untrue - at least for Oracle&apos;s implementation in jdk1.7.0_60 and in the following test. I created a test where I loop for 10 million times and I have a Deque of 10 million random Integers. Inside the loop I poll one element from and offer a constant element. On my computer, LinkedList is over 10 times slower than ArrayDeque and uses less memory). The reason is that unlike ArrayList, ArrayDeque keeps a pointer to the head of the array so that it doesn&apos;t have to move all elements when the head is removed.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
